  "final_answer": "The top 5 student groups by academic performance are:\n\n1. University students using AI for Learning\n   - Highest performance score: 2.643\n   - 85.7% reported improved grades\n   - Strong grade impact and solid satisfaction with AI tools\n   - Success appears driven by effective use of AI in moderate amounts, about 2.3 hours per day\n\n2. School students using AI for Coding\n   - Performance score: 2.455\n   - 72.7% reported improved grades\n   - Strong grade impact, good satisfaction, and relatively high AI usage\n   - Their success likely comes from frequent hands-on use of AI for problem-solving and practice\n\n3. College students using AI for Homework\n   - Performance score: 1.975\n   - 50.0% reported improved grades\n   - Strong positive grade impact with the highest daily usage among the top groups, about 4.3 hours\n   - Their results suggest that intensive AI support for assignments helps academic outcomes\n\n4. University students using AI for Research\n   - Performance score: 1.900\n   - 50.0% reported improved grades\n   - Strong satisfaction with AI tools and relatively high daily usage\n   - Their performance seems supported by using AI to assist with research tasks efficiently\n\n5. School students using AI for Learning\n   - Performance score: 1.867\n   - 50.0% reported improved grades\n   - Above-average satisfaction and steady AI usage of about 3.7 hours per day\n   - Their success appears linked to consistent AI-assisted learning habits\n\nKey factors across these top-performing groups:\n- Positive academic impact from AI use\n- Higher rates of students reporting improved grades\n- Good satisfaction with AI tools\n- Regular, purposeful AI usage, though not always extreme usage\n\nMost notable insight:\n- The strongest-performing group was University students using AI for Learning, suggesting that focused and efficient AI use for learning may deliver the best academic results.",
